<p>SINGAPORE - Residents across the island sweated it out at the GetActive! Singapore Heartland Festivals as they had a go at table tennis, skateboarding and zorbing, among other activities, on Saturday ahead of Singapore’s 58th birthday. </p>
<p>A total of about 28,000 people turned up for the ticketed events at four locations. The events kicked off at 4pm and ended at 9pm.</p>
<p>Organised by Sport Singapore and the National Day Parade 2023 Heartland Celebrations Committee, the festivals – which will continue on Sunday – were held at Bedok, Jurong West, Toa Payoh and Woodlands stadiums. The festival at Our Tampines Hub will take place only on Sunday. </p>
